collapsed\"\n|-\n! colspan=11 style=\"height:2.5em;\" | Limits for uncompressed RGB / {{YCbCr}} 4:4:4 video only\n|-\n! colspan=4 | Video Format\n! colspan=7 | Transmission Mode / Maximum Data Rate{{efn|Only a portion of DisplayPort's bandwidth is used for carrying video data. DisplayPort versions 1.0{{ndash}}1.4a use 8b/10b encoding, which means that 80% of the bits transmitted across the link represent data, and the other 20% are used for encoding purposes. The maximum bandwidth of RBR, HBR, HBR2, and HBR3 (6.48, 10.8, 21.6, and 32.4{{nbsp}}Gbit/s) therefore transport video data at rates of 5.184, 8.64, 17.28, and 25.92{{nbsp}}Gbit/s. DisplayPort version 2.0 uses 128b/132b encoding, and therefore the maximum bandwidths of UHBR 10, 13.5, and 20 (40, 54, and 80{{nbsp}}Gbit/s) transport data at rates of 39.69, 52.22, and 77.37{{nbsp}}Gbit/s.}}\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Shorthand\n! rowspan=2 | Resolution\n! rowspan=2 | Refresh<br />Rate (Hz)\n! rowspan=2 | Data Rate<br />Required{{efn|These data rates are for uncompressed 10{{nbsp}}bpc (30{{nbsp}}bit/px) color depth with RGB or YC<sub>B</sub>C<sub>R</sub> 4:4:4 color format and CVT-R2 timing. Uncompressed data rate for RGB video in bits per second is calculated as bits per pixel &times; pixels per frame &times; frames per second. Pixels per frame includes blanking intervals as defined by [[Coordinated Video Timings|CVT-R2]].}}\n! RBR\n! HBR\n! HBR2\n! HBR3\n! UHBR 10\n! UHBR 13.5\n! UHBR 20\n|-\n!5.184{{nbsp}}Gbit/s\n!8.64{{nbsp}}Gbit/s\n!17.28{{nbsp}}Gbit/s\n!25.92{{nbsp}}Gbit/s\n!38.69{{nbsp}}Gbit/s\n!52.22{{nbsp}}Gbit/s\n!77.37{{nbsp}}Gbit/s\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 1080p || rowspan=\"5\" | 1920{{resx}}1080 || align=\"right\"|60||align=\"right\"|4.00{{nbsp}}Gbit/s|| {{yes}} || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || {{yes}}\n|-\n|                                                     align=\"right\"|100||align=\"right\"|6.80{{nbsp}}Gbit/s|| {{no}} || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || {{yes