m)|Two Birds]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[One Stone]]'' (2018)\n* ''[[Barbara (Trixie Mattel album)|Barbara]]'' (2020)\n\n==Tours==\n*Ages 3 and Up {{small|(2015\u20132017)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timeout.com/chicago/blog/trixie-mattel-from-rupauls-drag-race-to-perform-in-chicago|title=Trixie Mattel from RuPaul's Drag Race to perform in Chicago|last1=Guerino|first1=Adam|date=June 9, 2015|website=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out Chicago]]|publisher=[[Time Out Group]]|access-date=March 31, 2018}}</ref>\n*Now with Moving Parts Tour (2018)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/therecord/2018/03/23/596143814/trixie-mattel-americas-next-top-folk-country-comedy-drag-artist|title=Trixie Mattel: America's Next Top Folk-Country Comedy Drag Artist|last1=Lorusso|first1=Marissa|date=March 23, 2018|website=[[NPR]]|publisher=|access-date=March 31, 2018}}</ref>\n*Super Bowl Cut {{small|(2018)}}\n*Skinny Legend Tour {{small|(2019)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/whats-on/music-nightlife-news/trixie-mattel-uk-tour-newcastle-14662258|title=Drag Race All Stars champion Trixie Mattel announces UK tour including date in Newcastle|last1=Duke|first1=Simon|date=May 15, 2018|website=[[Evening Chronicle]]|publisher=[[Reach plc]]|access-date=July 18, 2018}}</ref>\n*Grown Up Tour {{small|(2020)}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.etonline.com/trixie-mattel-is-all-grown-up-her-relationship-new-tour-and-all-the-other-moving-parts-exclusive |title=Trixie Mattel Is All 'Grown Up': Her Relationship, New Tour and All the Other Moving Parts (Exclusive) |last1=Kile |first1=Meredith B. |last2= |first2= |date=October 24, 2019 |website=[[Entertainment Tonight]] |publisher=[[CBS Television Distribution]] |access-date=December 17, 2019|archive-url=http://archive.is/rdxC0 |archive-date=December 17, 2019}}</ref>\n*UNHhhh Tour {{small| (with [[Katya Zamolodchikova|Katya]]) (2020)}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/australia-melbourne/article/Trixie-Katya-LIVE-The-UNHhhh-Tour-Is-Coming-To-Australia-20190715 |title=Trixie & Katya LIVE: The UNHhhh Tour! Is Coming To Australia |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=July 15, 2019 |website=[[BroadwayWorld]] |publisher= |access-date=December 17, 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/w0xl5 |archive-date=December 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" <!-- Do not center -->\n|- <!-- Never add unnecessary background colors -->\n! Year\n! Award Giving Body\n! Category\n! Work\n! Results\n! Ref.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|2017\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"|WOWIE Awards\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Best Drag Queen Music Video\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|\"Mama Don't Make Me Put On The Dress Again\"\n| {{win}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://worldofwonder.net/official-winners-list-wowie-awards-2017/|title=See The OFFICIAL Winners List From The WOWIE Awards 2017 Voted By YOU|work=Worldofwonder.net|date=December 8, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"|2018\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|The Screen Queen Award\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|\"Break Your Heart\"\n| {{win}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://worldofwonder.net/hold-on-to-your-wigs-its-the-2018-wowie-award-winners/|title=Hold on To Your Wigs! It\u2019s the 2018 WOWIE Award Winners!|work=Worldofwonder.net|date=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|[[James Beard Foundation Award]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Humor\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Herself\n| {{Nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jamesbeard.org/blog/the-2018-james-beard-award-nominees|title=THE 2018 JAMES BEARD AWARD NOMINEES|work=JamesBeard.org|date=March 14, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|2019\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|WOWIE Awards\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Best Beauty Line Awards\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Trixie Cosmetics\n| {{Nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://worldofwonder.net/cast-your-votes-in-world-of-wonders-2019-wowie-awards/|title=VOTING ENDS TODAY! Cast Your Votes NOW for World of Wonder\u2019s 2019 WOWIE Awards|work=Worldofwonder.net|date=November 29, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center\"|2020\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center\"|[[Queerty|''Queerties'' Awards]]\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Best Documentary\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|''Trixie Mattel: Moving Parts''\n| {{win}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.queerty.com/Queerties2020/|title='The 2020 Queerties|work=Cheat Sheet|date=February 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Drag Royalty\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Herself\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|Indie Music Video\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|\"Yellow Cloud\"\n| {{win}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Trixie Mattel}}\n* {{IMDb name|6083438|Brian Firkus}}\n* {{cite web | last=Mar | first=Pollo Del | title='Drag Race' Star Trixie Mattel's Campy Look, Quirky Style Saved Her Love for Drag | website=The Huffington Post |publisher=AOL, Inc.| date=May 30, 2016 | url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/pollo-del-mar/post_12034_b_10169646.html | ref=harv | accessdate=December 7, 2016}}\n* {{cite web | last=Mar | first=Pollo Del | title=Returning 'Drag Race' Star Trixie Mattel: My Elimination Made Fans Think the Competition Was Scripted | website=The Huffington Post  |publisher=AOL, Inc. | date=April 22, 2015 | url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/pollo-del-mar/post_9321_b_7111260.html | ref=harv | accessdate=December 7, 2016}}\n* {{cite web | title=Milwaukee drag superstar Trixie Mattel was on the 'American Horror Story' season finale | website=Milwaukee Record | date=November 18, 2016 | url=http://milwaukeerecord.com/film/milwaukee-drag-superstar-trixie-mattel-american-horror-story-season-finale/ | ref={{sfnref | Milwaukee Record | 2016}} | accessdate=December 7, 2016}}\n\n{{Trixie Mattel}}\n{{RuPaul's Drag Race}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mattel, Trixie}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American actors]]\n[[Category:American drag queens]]\n[[Category:Native American singers]]\n[[Category:Gay actors]]\n[[Category:LGBT entertainers from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT Native Americans]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Milwaukee]]\n[[Category:Ojibwe people]]\n[[Category:People from Crivitz, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars winners|Trixie Mattel]]\n[[Category:LGBT musicians from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT comedians]]\n[[Category:Singers from Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:LGBT singers]]\n[[Category:Gay musicians]]\n[[Category:Autoharp players]]\n[[Category:21st-century Native Americans]]\n[[Category:American cosmetics businesspeople]]\n[[Category:RuPaul's Drag Race contestants]]\n[[Category:Toy collectors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Trixie Mattel\n| image              = Rupaul Dragcon 2018-103 (41175949055) (cropped).jpg\n| caption            = Mattel at [[RuPaul's DragCon LA]] 2018\n| birth_name         = Brian Michael Firkus\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1989|8|23}}\n| birth_place        = [[Milwaukee]], [[Wisconsin]], U.S. \n| residence          = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| alma_mater         = [[University of Wisconsin\u2013Milwaukee]]\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Professional drag queen|singer-songwriter|comedian|television personality}}\n| yearsactive        = 2008\u2013present\n| known_for          = {{hlist|''[[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 7)|RuPaul's Drag Race]]''|''[[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 3)|RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars]]''|''[[UNHhhh]]''|''[[The Trixie & Katya Show]]''}}\n| predecessor        = [[Alaska Thunderfuck 5000|Alaska]]\n| successor          = [[Trinity Taylor]] and [[Mon\u00e9t X Change]]\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background = solo_singer\n| instrument = {{hlist|Vocals|guitar|clarinet|autoharp}}\n| genre = [[Country folk]], [[Americana (music)|Americana]]\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[Katya Zamolodchikova]]|[[Bob the Drag Queen]]|[[Pearl (drag queen)|Pearl]]|[[Kim Chi (drag queen)|Kim Chi]]|[[RuPaul]]}}\n| label =\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Trixie Mattel''' is the drag persona of '''Brian Michael Firkus''' (born August 23, 1989),<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/trixie-mattel-mn0003634361/biography|title=Trixie Martel : Biography|last1=Monger|first1=James Christopher|date=August 2017|publisher=[[AllMusic.com]] ([[All Media Network]])|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> an American [[drag queen]], singer-songwriter, comedian, and [[television personality]] from [[Milwaukee]], [[Wisconsin]]. Mattel is known for being the winner of the [[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 3)|third season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars]]'', and for placing sixth on the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 7)|seventh season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]''.\n\nMattel co-hosts the [[web series]] ''[[UNHhhh]]'' and its [[Viceland]] follow-up ''[[The Trixie & Katya Show]]'' alongside [[Katya Zamolodchikova]]. Her first studio album, ''[[Two Birds (album)|Two Birds]]'', was released in 2017, followed by her second album, ''[[One Stone]]'', in 2018. Her third album, ''[[Barbara (Trixie Mattel album)|Barbara]]'' was released February 7, 2020.\n\nMattel is also the CEO of Trixie Cosmetics, her cosmetics brand.\n\n==Early life==\nFirkus was born in [[Milwaukee]], [[Wisconsin]].<ref name=\"allmusic\" /> He is half [[Ojibwe]] and comes from a [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] family living in [[Crivitz, Wisconsin]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Brooke|first1=Zach|title=Point of View: Trixie Mattel|url= https://www.milwaukeemag.com/2015/09/08/qa-trixie-mattel/|website=[[Milwaukee Magazine]]|publisher=[[Quad/Graphics]]|date=September 8, 2015|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>[https://webelieveproject.wordpress.com/2015/05/13/when-you-are-true-to-yourself-amazing-things-can-happen/ When you are true to yourself amazing things can happen | This We Believe] Retrieved September 10, 2018.</ref> He had an abusive stepfather who would call him a \"trixie\" when he acted feminine, which would later inspire his drag name. He almost went by the name Cupcake before deciding on Trixie.<ref>{{mattel|title=Living Doll: Trixie Mattel|work=[[Metro Weekly]]|publisher=|accessdate=May 5, 2015}}</ref> After graduating high school, Firkus attended the [[University of Wisconsin\u2013Milwaukee]], where he received a BFA in Music Theatre<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wisconsingazette.com/entertainment/for-brian-firkus-a-childhood-slur-became-the-springboard-for/article_73f168f7-1e1c-567a-8386-e1acc6fcdb2e.html |title=For Brian Firkus, a childhood slur became the springboard for success as Trixie Mattel  |last1=Kennedy |first1=Kerrie |date=June 3, 2015 |website=Wisconsin Gazette |publisher= |accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> and was introduced to drag while performing in a production of ''[[The Rocky Horror Show]]'' at the [[Oriental Theatre (Milwaukee)|Oriental Theatre]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyxtra.com/a-filthy-starry-night-with-trixie-mattel-67999|title=A filthy, starry night with Trixie Mattel|last1=Yerxa |first1=Mike |date=June 25, 2015|website=[[Daily Xtra]]|publisher=[[Pink Triangle Press]]|access-date=August 12, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nHe first performed in drag in 2008, at LaCage NiteClub in Milwaukee.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://host.madison.com/ct/news/local/city-life/plan-b-host-trixie-mattel-to-strut-her-stuff-on/article_8cf12a91-fe1b-5ddf-bcf3-f30d750ae206.html |title=Plan B host Trixie Mattel to strut her stuff on 'RuPaul's Drag Race' |last1=Christians |first1=Lindasy |date=December 10, 2014 |website=[[The Capital Times]] |publisher= |accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> Firkus became a staple of the Milwaukee drag scene while also performing in [[Chicago]] alongside other acts introduced on ''RuPaul's Drag Race'', such as [[Kim Chi (drag queen)|Kim Chi]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.jsonline.com/entertainment/arts/milwaukee-drag-queen-trixie-mattel-wins-spot-on-rupauls-drag-race-b99404841z1-285037501.html |title=Milwaukee drag queen Trixie Mattel wins spot on \"RuPaul's Drag Race\" |last1=Schumacher |first1=Mary Louise |date=December 7, 2014 |website=[[Milwaukee Journal Sentinel]] |publisher=[[Gannett Company]] |accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/rupauls-drag-race-queens-best-friends/|title=RuPaul's Drag Race: 7 Queens Who Are Best Friends (And 8 Who Are Frenemies)|date=April 15, 2018|website=ScreenRant|language=en-US|access-date=January 16, 2019}}</ref> In 2014, Firkus attended [[Aveda|The Institute of Beauty and Wellness]] before withdrawing later that same year to participate in ''RuPaul's Drag Race''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timeout.com/chicago/blog/trixie-mattel-from-rupauls-drag-race-to-perform-in-chicago |title=Trixie Mattel from RuPaul's Drag Race to perform in Chicago |last1=Guerino |first1=Adam |date=June 9, 2015 |website=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]] |publisher= |accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n===''RuPaul's Drag Race''===\nAs a competitor in [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 7)|Season 7]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]'', Mattel was eliminated in episode four and later reentered the competition in episode eight by winning the \"Conjoined Twins\" challenge with [[Pearl (drag queen)|Pearl Liaison]]. Mattel was once again eliminated in episode 10,<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/matthew-terrell/trixie-mattel-elimination_b_6936636.html|title=Trixie Mattel Elimination Casts Doubt on RPDR Reality|last1=Terrell|first1=Matthew|date=March 26, 2015|website=[[HuffPost|The Huffington Post]]|publisher=AOL Inc|access-date=December 4, 2016}}</ref> placing sixth overall and becoming the first queen to last more than one episode after returning to the competition.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nMattel later returned for the [[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 3)|third season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race: All Stars]]'', which started airing on January 25, 2018. On March 15, 2018, her fellow competitors voted for her to advance to the final two, where she ultimately won against runner-up [[Kennedy Davenport]] in the final lipsync battle.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tvline.com/2018/03/15/rupauls-drag-race-all-stars-trixie-mattel-wins-season-3-finale-recap/|title=RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars Finale: Did the Right Queen Win Season 3?|last=Swift|first=Andy|date=March 16, 2018|work=TVLine|access-date=March 16, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/921102/rupaul-s-drag-race-all-stars-3-crowns-a-winner|title=RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars 3 Crowns a Winner|work=E! Online|access-date=March 16, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nShe competed in the 2018 television special ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race Holi-slay Spectacular]]'' and won alongside the other competitors.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8482663/rupauls-drag-race-holiday-spectacular-trixie-shangela|title=Kim Chi, Shangela, Trixie Mattel & More to Compete in 'RuPaul's Drag Race Holi-Slay Spectacular'|work=Billboard|access-date=November 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZSbFfSm0DgM|title=YouTube|website=www.youtube.com|access-date=January 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Other ventures===\n[[File:Trixie and Katya's High School Reunion 3.jpg|thumb|right|[[Katya Zamolodchikova]] with Trixie Mattel]]\nAfter competing on ''Drag Race'', on December 31, 2015, Mattel guest starred in a special edition of [[World of Wonder (production company)|WOWPresents]]' Fashion Photo Review<ref>{{Citation|last=WOWPresents|title=Trixie & Katya's Fashion Photo RuView, RuView of Raja & Raven|date=December 31, 2015|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xUtKgqq4epM&index=1&list=PLVmMNOHpsWfkF7E-ZYg_mufJfF6_xJBim|access-date=February 21, 2019}}</ref> with fellow season seven contestant [[Katya Zamolodchikova]], which later launched ''[[UNHhhh]]'', that premiered on March 25, 2016. The duo later went on to star in ''[[The Trixie & Katya Show]]'', which premiered on [[Viceland]] on November 15, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.papermag.com/hold-on-to-your-wigs-katya-and-trixie-mattel-are-getting-their-own-tv-show-2474558266.html|title=Hold On to Your Wigs: Katya and Trixie Mattel Are Getting Their Own TV Show|last1=Cuby|first1=Michael|date=August 18, 2017|work=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/trixie-and-katya-show-tvs-best-new-talk-show-hosts-are-two-drag-queens|title='Trixie and Katya Show': TV's Best New Talk Show Hosts Are Two Drag Queens|first=Kevin|last=Fallon|date=November 15, 2017|publisher=|via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref> Also in November 2017, Trixie and Katya starred in a drag stage adaptation of the 1997 cult film ''[[Romy and Michele's High School Reunion]]'', entitled ''Trixie and Katya's High School Reunion''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newnownext.com/trixie-mattel-katya-romy-michele-high-school-reunion/11/2017/|title=Trixie Mattel And Katya Recreated The \"Romy And Michele\" Dance Sequence\u2014And It Was Perfection|website=newnownext.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldofwonder.net/absolutely-hysterical-trixie-katya-recreate-romy-michele-dance-sequence/|title=Absolutely Hysterical: Trixie & Katya Recreate that Iconic \"Romy And Michele\" Dance Sequence|date=November 21, 2017|website=worldofwonder.net}}</ref>\n\nMattel has toured around the world with her stand-up comedy show called \"Ages 3 and Up\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.trixiemattel.com/event/trixie-mattel-ages-3-and-up/|title=\"Trixie Mattel: Ages 3 and Up\" {{!}} Trixie Mattel|work=Trixie Mattel|access-date=October 16, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> In October 2017, Mattel streamed on the live video gaming platform [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] alongside 8BitDylan to raise money for the [[GaymerX]] foundation and many other charities before and since.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/EightBitDylan/status/916009357954789376|title=This Sunday catch @trixiemattel and myself play some games to raise money for the @GaymerX foundation! 6PM CST|last=(8Bit)|first=Dylan|date=October 5, 2017|website=@EightBitDylan|language=en|access-date=December 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\nTrixie has toured on the \"Haters Roast: The Shady Tour\" with other queens from ''RuPaul's Drag Race'', such as [[Jinkx Monsoon]] and [[Thorgy Thor]] for their 2017 and 2018 alumni tours.\n\nIn February 2018, she announced her new comedy tour \"Now with Moving Parts\", which began in April 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/trixiemattel/status/966038334576386048|title=First 9 cities announced! DragFans.com|date=February 20, 2018|website=@trixiemattel|language=en|access-date=February 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\nA documentary film titled ''[[Trixie Mattel: Moving Parts]]'' premiered at the [[Tribeca Film Festival]] in April 2019, and screened until May 2019. It documents Mattel as she embarks on her \"Moving Parts\" tour following her ''All Stars'' win, as well as her personal struggles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8501229/trixie-mattel-documentary-2019-tribeca-film-festival-premiere|title=Trixie Mattel Documentary Set to Premiere at 2019 Tribeca Film Festival|date=March 5, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 25, 2019}}</ref> The documentary will be available on [[Video On Demand]] platforms on December 3, 2019. An accompanying acoustic soundtrack is set for release later in December.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/movies/2019/11/15/trixie-mattel-moving-parts-release-date/|title=Trixie Mattel's Moving Parts documentary finally has a release date|last=Nolfi|first=Joey|publisher=Entertainment Weekly|date=November 15, 2019|accessdate=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn May 1, 2019, Mattel announced that she will be releasing her make-up brand \"Trixie Cosmetics\" later that month, with the products launching at RuPaul's DragCon LA on May 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.out.com/celebs/2019/5/01/trixie-mattel-launching-her-own-beauty-brand|title=Trixie Mattel Is Launching Her Own Beauty Brand|magazine=[[Out (magazine)|Out]]|last=Dommu|first=Rose|publisher=Joe Landry|date=May 1, 2019|accessdate=May 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2019, Mattel was one of 37 queens to be featured on the cover of [[New York Magazine]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nymag.com/press/2019/06/on-the-cover-the-most-powerful-drag-queens-in-america.html|title=On New York's 37 Covers: The Most Powerful Drag Queens in America|date=June 10, 2019|website=New York Press Room}}</ref>\n\nMattel's first comedy special, ''Trixie Mattel: Skinny Legend'', aired on [[OutTV]] in Canada on September 26, 2019.<ref name=\"Rudolph\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newnownext.com/drag-race-comedy-specials-out-tv-trixie-mattel/07/2019/|title=\"Drag Race\" Alums Return to TV in New Documentary, Comedy Specials|last=Rudolph|first=Christopher|publisher=NewNowNext|date=July 24, 2019|accessdate=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Music===\nMattel released the [[country folk]] album ''[[Two Birds (album)|Two Birds]]'' in May 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/two-birds/id1225829683|title=Two Birds by Trixie Mattel on iTunes|publisher=iTunes|language=en|access-date=April 30, 2017}}</ref> Her second album, ''[[One Stone]]'', was released on March 15, 2018, the same night as the ''RuPaul's Drag Race: All Stars'' finale.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/trixie-mattel-interview-one-stone-drag-race-all-stars_uk_5aaa58bce4b0f4aaa1141bbe|title=Trixie Mattel Reflects On Her 'All Stars' Performance And New Album 'One Stone'|date=March 15, 2018|work=HuffPost UK|access-date=March 16, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\nSpeaking to ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', Mattel listed her primary influences as [[June Carter Cash]] and [[Dolly Parton]] and states that she grew up on the music of [[George Jones]], [[Conway Twitty]] and [[Johnny Cash]]. She is also a fan of [[Jason Isbell]], [[Kris Kristofferson]], [[Aimee Mann]] and [[Kacey Musgraves]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/country/features/rupaul-drag-race-trixie-mattel-country-albums-kacey-musgraves-w518524|title=Drag Queen Trixie Mattel on Her Country Albums, Kacey Musgraves Obsession|website=rollingstone.com|date=March 29, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn a September 2018 interview with ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', she announced that she is working on her third studio album that will feature an \"[[electro-folk]]\" sound and is going to be called ''[[Barbara (Trixie Mattel album)|Barbara]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8474050/trixie-mattel-electro-folk-album-eminem|title=Trixie Mattel Talks Upcoming 'Electro-Folk' Album & Shares Erotic Eminem Fantasy|website=Billboard}}</ref> \"Yellow Cloud\" was released as the first single from the album on May 17, 2019, though it was later revealed to be a non-album single. On January 10, 2020, the album's release date was confirmed for February 7, 2020, alongside the album tracklist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8547761/trixie-mattel-barbara-album-teaser-video|title=Trixie Mattel Is Bringing Fans to the Beach With Official 'Barbara' Album Teaser: Watch|website=Billboard|last=Daw|first=Stephen|date=January 10, 2020|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nFirkus is openly [[gay]].<ref>{{cite tweet|number=888511437009698817|user=trixiemattel|title=I'm a gay person who specializes in gay activities.|date=July 21, 2017}}</ref> He has been in a relationship with filmmaker David Silver, who is the producer of his documentary, ''Moving Parts'', for three years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.queerty.com/trixie-mattel-time-moms-boyfriend-pulled-gun-teen-queen-20190428|title= Trixie Mattel on Katya\u2019s mental breakdown caught on film in her dragumentary, \u2018Moving Parts\u2019|website=Queerty|last=Reddish|first=David|date=April 28, 2019|accessdate=October 27, 2019}}</ref> He is also a [[vegetarian]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=trixiemattel|number=610533359714893824|title=I'm a vegetarian !|date=June 15, 2015|accessdate=September 19, 2018|url-status=live|archivedate=May 19, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180519175211/https://twitter.com/trixiemattel/status/610533359714893824}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|accessdate=September 19, 2018|user=trixiemattel|number=1012961007453528067|title=Triggered. Also I\u2019m a vegetarian.|date=June 30, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180920022742/https://twitter.com/trixiemattel/status/1012961007453528067|archivedate=September 20, 2018}}</ref> Trixie Mattel has an obsession over [[Barbie|Barbie Dolls]], owning a wide collection of Barbies in her Los Angeles home.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.avclub.com/trixie-mattel-on-the-nostalgic-dolls-that-inspired-her-1840489833|title=Trixie Mattel on the Barbies that inspired her upcoming world tour|first=Marah|last=Eakin|date=December 19, 2019|website=AV Club|access-date=February 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n! {{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| 2015\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]''\n| Herself (contestant)\n| [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 7)|Season 7]], 6th place\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2015/mar/03/rupauls-drag-race-recap-season-seven-episode-one-the-devil-wears-nada|title=RuPaul's Drag Race recap: season seven, episode one \u2013 the devil wears nada|last1=Carpentier |first1=Megan |last2=Rushe |first2=Dominic|work=[[The Guardian]]|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|date=March 3, 2015|accessdate=June 7, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| Herself (guest)\n| [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 8)|Season 8]], Episode 10: \"Grand Finale\"\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[RuPaul's Drag Race: Untucked]]''\n|Herself\n|Season 7\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n|''[[American Horror Story: Roanoke]]''\n|Herself\n|Season 6, Episode 10: \"[[Chapter 10 (American Horror Story)|Chapter 10]]\"\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newnownext.com/american-horror-story-trixie-mattel/11/2016/ |title=Trixie Mattel Pops Up In The \"American Horror Story\" Season Finale |last1=Avery |first1=Dan |date=November 17, 2016 |website=[[Logo TV#Online|NewNowNext]] |publisher=[[Viacom Media Networks]] |accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Gay for Play Game Show Starring RuPaul]]''\n|Herself\n|Season 1, Episode 5: \"Featuring Mindy Cohn\"<br>Season 2, Episode 2: \"Featuring Frankie Grande\"\n|\n|-\n|2017\u20132018\n|''[[The Trixie & Katya Show]]''\n|Herself (co-host)\n|14 episodes\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vulture.com/2017/08/trixie-mattel-and-katya-are-getting-their-own-show-honey.html |title=Honey, RuPaul's Drag Race Contestants Trixie Mattel and Katya Are Getting Their Own Viceland Show, Honey |last1=McHenry |first1=Jackson |date=August 18, 2017 |website=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] |publisher=New York Media, LLC |accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[RuPaul's Drag Race: All Stars]]''\n|Herself (contestant)\n|[[RuPaul's Drag Race: All Stars (season 3)|Season 3]], Winner\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 10)|RuPaul's Drag Race]]''\n|Herself (guest)\n|Season 10, Episode 1: \"10s Across The Board\"\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ew.com/tv/2018/03/21/katya-bob-the-drag-queen-return-drag-race-season-10/ |title=Katya, Bob the Drag Queen, more return fo